FBIS4-33546 "drlat110_a_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-110 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Seeks To Expand Bilateral Relations Seeks To Expand Bilateral Relations FL0706183094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 6 Jun 94 FL0706183094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Report by correspondant Ilia Sardina from the "Exclusive" program] [Text] A CPC delegation headed by Wu Bangguo, Politburo member and Party secretary in Shanghai, arrived in Cuba today at the invitation of the Communist Party of Cuba. The delegation was met at Jose Marti International Airport by Politburo members Carlos Lage and Jose Ramon Balaguer. Wu Bangguo said this visit seeks to strengthen and expand traditional ties between the two peoples and parties: [Begin Wu recording in Mandarin with superimposed Spanish translation] We have a lot in common. That is why I have arrived with great interest in Cuba. We have arrived in Cuba with the friendly feelings of the CPC and the Chinese [word indistinct] and our visit seeks to promote relations between the two countries even more. [end recording] The delegation will visit health care, agroindustrial, cultural, and tourism officials in Havana, as well as in Cienfuegos and in Matanzas.
